# <type>: <subject> (50 chars or less)
# Example: fix: resolve authentication error on login

# <body> (Wrap at 72 chars)
# Explain *what* changed and *why* (not how - the code shows that)


# <footer>
# Include any issue references, breaking changes, or co-authors


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Type can be:
#   feat     - New feature
#   fix      - Bug fix
#   docs     - Documentation changes
#   style    - Code style changes (formatting, semicolons, etc)
#   refactor - Code refactoring (no functional changes)
#   perf     - Performance improvements
#   test     - Adding or updating tests
#   build    - Build system or dependency changes
#   ci       - CI/CD configuration changes
#   chore    - Other changes that don't modify src or test files
#
# Best Practices:
# - Use imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adds")
# - Don't end subject line with a period
# - Separate subject from body with a blank line
# - Focus on the "why" not the "what" in the body
# - Reference issues and PRs in the footer
#
# Example commit message:
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# feat: add user authentication with OAuth 2.0
#
# Implement OAuth 2.0 authentication to improve security and enable
# single sign-on capabilities. This replaces the previous basic auth
# system which had security limitations.
#
# The implementation uses the industry-standard oauth2 library and
# supports Google, GitHub, and Microsoft providers.
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: Basic auth endpoints have been removed
# Closes #123
# Co-authored-by: Jane Doe <jane@example.com>
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────